  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "For the test below, the correct log data would be `0x20, 0x01, \"f\"`. However, legacy codegen returns `\"f\", 0x20, 0x01, \"f\"` i.e., an extra `\"f\"` is prefixed.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract C {\r\n  event ev1(bytes ep0);\r\n  fallback() external {\r\n  assembly {\r\n    calldatacopy(0, 5, 0x60)\r\n  }\r\n  emit ev1(bytes(\"f\"));\r\n }\r\n}\r\n// ====\r\n// compileViaYul: also\r\n// ----\r\n// () ->\r\n// ~ emit ev1(bytes): \"f\", 0x20, 0x01, \"f\"\r\n```",
